==Dutch==
===Etymology===
From {{etyl|dum|nl}} {{term|sullen|lang=dum}}, from {{etyl|odt|nl}} *{{term||skulan|lang=odt}}, {{term|sulan|lang=odt}}, from {{proto|Germanic|skulanan|lang=nl}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈzʏ.lə(n)/|lang=nl}}

===Verb===
{{nl-verb|pp}}

# {{context|lang=nl|auxiliary|present tense}} [[will]]. Used to form the [[future tense]] of a verb, together with an [[infinitive]].
#: ''Het '''zal''' toch niet werken.''
#:: It '''will''' not work anyway.
#: ''Dat '''zal''' niet gebeuren.''
#:: That '''will''' not happen.
#: '''Note:''' [[gaan]] is also used for the future tense, instead of zullen.
# {{context|lang=nl|auxiliary|past tense}} [[would]]. Used to form the [[conditional mood]] of a verb, together with an infinitive.
#: ''Het werk '''zou''' nu af zijn geweest als jij je niet had verslapen.''
#:: The work '''would''' have been finished now if you hadn't overslept.
#: ''Dat '''zou''' ik niet doen als ik jou was.''
#:: I '''would''' not do that if I were you.
# {{context|lang=nl|modal auxiliary}} Used to indicate [[intent]] or [[disposition]] to perform an action in the [[future]]: [[will]], [[shall]], be [[going to]].
#: ''Het '''zou''' vandaag regenen.''
#:: It '''was going to''' rain today.
#: '''''Zal''' ik eerst gaan?''
#:: '''Shall''' I go first?

